    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Collection consists of materials relating to Fort A.P. Hill, Blacksburg, South Hill, Virginia art and artists such as Betty Branch and Tedd Blevins, Bassett Furniture Company, First Baptist Church in Salem,
Route 58 in Grayson County, outdoor activities, theater, and Roanoke Democratic Party politics. The Fort A. P. Hill materials include archeological and architectural surveys, an installation diary from 1941-1945,
a history of the army base, and photographs of buildings.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement
</head>
      <p>Organized into the following series: I. Fort A.P. Hill; II. Miscellaneous.
</p>
    </arrangement>
